I have been to this location on several occasions, and the food is pretty good. The taste has been pretty consistent and food is always freshly prepared. Their food is reasonably priced and the lemonades are amazing. The only reason why they're receiving four stars is due to their lack of customer service.  As previously stated, my only gripe is the customer service. On two separate occasions, the owner's younger brother (unsure of his name) has been very rude, ignorant, and disrespectful to customers and even workers. I have personally witnessed him yelling and arguing with a lady who was a customer, which was very unprofessional and uncomfortable to watch. He talks about his black customers to other customers by generalizing all ”black people” by using negative stereotypes. He belittles his workers by talking to them disrespectfully as he is superior to his workers. Demanding them to do things in an aggressive tone and/or matter. Witnessing all of this has turned me off from coming to this establishment. I’m not sure if he realizes their business is located in a prominently black community and black people are the ones who support him and buy from him. It saddens me to witness him carry on and belittle his own people this way.  Also, on one occasion, my partner and I order two meals (multiple fish shrimps fries) and was given two small half-filled containers of tarter sauce and requested if we could have more since that wasn’t enough for our meals. He gave us two more small containers and says to us, “next time I’ll have to charge you”. Which left a bitter taste in my mouth and I was thrown aback by his statement.  This type of behavior is unacceptable. I would rather my review focuses mainly on their food, and it saddens me to leave this review, and hopefully, the owners see this and make changes immediately. This review was not left to bash a black-owned business because I always support my own people.  My suggestion is to have the original guy (brother) to take over again. The service was better and he was very professional. Also, it's just tartar sauce, stop complaining/being possessive with sauce when people spending a minimum $30 dollar in your establishment. That’s uncalled for and would make people not want to do business with you.

Excellent... First the smell from outside was lured me.. Went inside and the place was immaculate and I noticed the reasonably priced menu.  Food looked good and smelled excellent so it took me a while to decide what to eat.  Ended up getting fish with shrimp and onion rings.  The food looked amazing, I couldn't wait.  Tasted the shrimp first, it was crispy and amazingly draine seasoned so I couldn't wait to try the fish.  It was great.  Fried nice and crispy, seasoned well and not greasy at all. The only suggestion I have is I think they should make a signature onion ring, perhaps something bet battered.  The onion rings were good and blessed with their sensational seasoning but they were regular onion rings.  I just feel like everything else was so star studded the onion rings should've delivered in the same way.  Nevertheless, I'll definitely be back.  I hopeto have them cater something for me in the future.
